0.5.0

## Features
- Nil-channel analysis (NIL001) wired into check/compile/build/LSP
- Non-exhaustive match is a compile error (EXHAUST003)
- Effect rows on prelude builtins; body effect inference
- Nominal newtypes (`type T = newtype U`) for branded trading IDs
- Trading safety design doc and expanded examples

## Breaking changes
- EXHAUST003 now fails `goop check`
- NIL001 fails check when channel used before init
- Functions with `with {}` cannot call IO without error
- Existing code may need `with { io }` on functions using print_line

## Migration
- Add `with { io }` to mains/helpers that print
- Add missing match arms for ADTs
- Use `type foo = newtype string` for order IDs and symbols
